@dev Returns an array of `Property` objects owned by the caller of the function.
 @return An array of `Property` objects owned by the caller of the function.

createDiagnostic(address,string,string,u.details: Function to create a new diagnostic, mint a token associated with it, and set the document hash.

params._documentHash: The hash of the document related to the diagnostic.
params._expiryDate: The expiration date of the diagnostic.
params._property: The address of the Property contract associated with the diagnostic.
params._tokenURI: The URI for the token metadata.

returns._0: tokenId The ID of the newly minted token associated with the diagnostic.

createProperty(string,string).details: Function to create a new Property contract and store its reference.

params._name: The name of the Property contract.
params._symbol: The symbol of the Property contract.

returns._0: propertyAddress The address of the newly created Property contract.

getDiagnosticHash(address,uint256).details: Returns the document hash associated with the given property and token ID.

params.property: The address of the Property contract.
params.tokenId: The ID of the token representing the diagnostic report.

returns._0: A string representing the document hash associated with the diagnostic report.

getPropertyContract(address).details: Returns the Property contract associated with the given property address.

params.property: The address of the Property contract.

returns._0: A `Property` object representing the Property contract.

getUserProperties().details: Returns an array of `Property` objects owned by the caller of the function.

returns._0: An array of `Property` objects owned by the caller of the function.

transferOwnership(address,address,uint25.details: Transfers ownership of a token representing a diagnostic report to a new owner.

params._property: The address of the Property contract.
params._to: The address of the new owner.
params._tokenId: The ID of the token representing the diagnostic report.

userdoc.notice: TPropertyFactory is a smart contract that manages the creation of  Property contracts and the minting of diagnostics as ERC721 tokens. The contract allows users to create new Property contracts, create diagnostic tokens with a document hash and token URI, and transfer tokens between users. Each user can have multiple Property contracts, and each contract can have multiple diagnostic tokens associated with it.
